               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus account of money taxes from the Arsinoites (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt. Payments are in money. Roses, snowdrops and other flowers are grown on some of the taxed property Verso has an account in Demotic (P.Duk.inv. 700 V)</summary>
